00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:46.290
Well, they're in series, and
series resistors, they just

00:03:46.290 --> 00:03:47.710
add up together, right?

00:03:47.710 --> 00:03:50.770
So the combined resistance of
this 2-ohm resistor and this

00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:53.510
1-ohm resistor is just
a 3-ohm resistor.

00:03:53.510 --> 00:03:57.580
So let's erase and simplify.

00:03:57.580 --> 00:04:02.280
So then we get that combined
resistor, right?

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:05.360
We had the 2-ohm that we
had simplified and

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:06.610
then we had a 1-ohm.

00:04:12.200 --> 00:04:15.250
So we had a 2-ohm and a 1-ohm
in series, so those simplify

00:04:15.250 --> 00:04:16.880
to 3 ohms.

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:19.300
Well, now this is getting
really simple.

00:04:19.300 --> 00:04:23.670
So what do these two resistors
simplify to?

00:04:23.670 --> 00:04:27.710
Well, 1 over their combined
resistance is

00:04:27.710 --> 00:04:31.040
